Step into the Shade

In the Summer temperatures can climb to dangerous heights, which can have negative health implications. As climate change increases severe weather events like heat waves, it will become more important to know how to beat the summer heat.

When summer temperatures rise one of the best ways to stay cool is to find a shady area. Most of the parks in North Vancouver have tree cover which helps to create shaded safe havens from the sun. This app can help you find cool areas within the city and show you which areas to avoid.

This can be done by:
          (1) selecting the tree symbol on the upper right to enter an address

          (2) selecting the location finder on the upper left to find parks and water bodies nearby

Strenuous activity should be limited during the warmest times of the day, for this reason the parks with lighting are noted so you can find somewhere to exercise after the sun goes down. Select the lamp symbol in the upper right to find sports fields.
